The Chairman of Gwagwalada Area Council, Alhaji Adamu Mustapha Denze, has described the Igbo community in the area as critical stakeholders in political, economic and social activities. The chairman stated this when he received in audience the leadership of Igbo traditional council led by Chief  Eric Onah, who paid him a courtesy visit in his office yesterday. He said unity and harmonious relationship should always be the watch word of every individual irrespective of religious and ethnic affiliations, adding that as citizens, there was the need to love one another. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE The chairman commended the Igbo community for their continuous support to his administration, assuring them that his administration would always carry them along in policies and programmes. The Eze Igbo of Gwagwalada, Chief Eric Onah, commended  the chairman for his efforts towards addressing infrastructural challenges in the area. He assured the chairman of  the Igbo’s support towards ensuring that he delivered dividends of democracy to the people at the grassroots. The Igbo chief later presented a congratulatory card to the chairman over his victory during the last council election in the area.  Igbos in AMAC tasked on unity LG Chairman tasks traditional rulers on security Abaji chair approves increase in village chiefs’ salaries Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin